</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1044,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">
Male terminalia. 
<number box="[390,404,1047,1071]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="8.0">8</number>
th tergite truncated on posterior margin; 
<number box="[843,857,1047,1071]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="8.0">8</number>
th sternite, 
<number box="[971,985,1047,1071]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="9.0">9</number>
th and 
<number box="[1050,1078,1047,1071]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="10.0">10</number>
th tergites with two regions more sclerotized (Fig. 
<number box="[340,354,1087,1111]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="2.0">2</number>
A, B); 
<number box="[437,451,1087,1111]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="8.0">8</number>
th sternite with bristles on the posterior region (Fig. 
<number box="[1024,1038,1087,1111]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="2.0">2</number>
A). Aedeagus, dorso-ventrally flat; basal piece longer than parameres, only the basal region fused ventrally; (Fig. 
<number box="[1060,1074,1122,1146]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="2.0">2</number>
C, D); parameres ventrally not fused; medial lobe with proximal apodemes beginning on the posterior third of the basal piece; bridge absent (Fig. 
<number box="[151,166,1194,1218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="2.0">2</number>
C, D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1044,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">
Female terminalia. Coxites with short bristles dorsally; internal margin carinate (
<figureCitation box="[1126,1194,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1370,1392]" captionTargetBox="[201,1394,273,1342]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[184,1403,267,1349]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hister lucia sp. nov., female. A. Coxites, ventral view; B. Coxites, dorsal view (scales: 0.25 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241370/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="440">
Fig. 
<number box="[1180,1194,1231,1255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="440" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B). Spermatheca, spermathecal gland, bursa copulatrix and common oviduct were not observed.
</paragraph>
